        "created_at": "2022-07-23T15:49:00.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=3875375&amp;iNote=9949142\"><strong>2019 Dureuil-Janthial Bourgogne Blanc</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, Bourgogne Blanc (7/23/2022)</em><br>\nA slight, pleasant reduction gives way to aromas of pear, gardenias, freesias, vanilla bean, and raw feuilletage. Medium full bodied on the palate with a surprising mid palate weight for a modest Bourgogne blanc with a lively acid structure. There\u2019s certainly some oak that pokes through after the reduction blows off, and the alcohol noticeable when focused on, but overall balanced and enjoyable</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Closure: natural cork<br>\nABV: 14.5%<br>\nStem: Grassl Cru<br>\nDecant: N/A; consumed over the course of an evening</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 5,
        "updated_at": "2022-08-15T21:24:32.650Z",
